text: Egzona Zeka (born 25 April 1997) is an Albanian–Kosovan footballer who plays as a forward for Women's League club KFF Mitrovica and the Kosovo women's national team. She was a member of the Albania women's national team before Kosovo being accepted as a member of UEFA and FIFA. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football forwards Category:Kosovan women's footballers Category:Albanian women's footballers Category:Albania women's international footballers Category:KFF Mitrovica players
